						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Pokun wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">One thing FCEUX is missing though is an OAM viewer.</div><br />I used to miss an OAM viewer too; but, after understanding that page 2 is jammed into OAM each frame using the OAM_DMA register, $4014, taking 513 cycles, I just check page 2 in the hex editor to look at OAM.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> <br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">sprite = $200</div><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">.MACRO update_sprite<br />lda #&gt;sprite<br />sta $4014<br />.ENDM</div>using asm6<br /><br />edit: I don't understand most of this thread, but I'm happy your problem is solved! <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /></div>

