				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Many games use the same map for display and for collisions. It's very reasonable to assume that blocks that look the same will behave the same, so you actually save a lot of space by defining the collision information only once for each type of block, instead of multiple times, once for each instance of each type of block.<br /><br />Depending on how your levels are compressed, you can read the collision information directly from ROM without problems. If you use something that doesn't allow random access though, such as RLE or LZ, then it does make sense to buffer a small section of the level in RAM, and update that as the player walks around.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
