				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I believe I use a similar trick when calculating sprite coordinates, to compensate for the fact that sprites are positioned one scanline lower than the Y coordinate specified in their OAM entries. Instead of doing <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">SpriteY = ObjectY - CameraY</tt>, I do <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">SpriteY = ObjectY - CameraY - 1</tt> by putting a CLC before the subtraction, instead of the usual SEC.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

